    arm64: dts: qcom: add Canoe TLMM

    Describe the Canoe top-level pin controller at 0x0f000000 using the
    dedicated driver and binding already present in the tree.

    Wire the summary interrupt to GIC SPI 208, use the merged PDC as the
    wakeup parent, expose all 218 GPIOs through gpio-ranges, and translate
    the firmware-owned GPIO list into mainline gpio-reserved-ranges tuples.

    Limit this milestone to the TLMM provider itself; pin states and
    peripheral consumers remain out of scope.

    Signed-off-by: Travis Mills <travismills82@gmail.com>
